вЌќ Properly set up a newly-created object, starting with it's required system control information
вЌќ It must be called directly(!) from the creating-class namespace.
вЌќ? (Watch out if it's a special-case class type such as ActiveX or Dyalog)
вЌќ
вЌќ "object" should be a two-item vector containing the following items:
вЌќ       [1] Reference to the parent object
вЌќ       [2] Reference to the just-created object (not its name at this point)

 (parent object)в†ђobject вЌќ Separate object references
 :While 0в‰ parent.вЋ•NC'_Owner' вЌќ If this is an intermediate hidden parent object... вЌќ? When does this occur?
     parentв†ђparent._Owner вЌќ Redirect parentage up to its APL+Win parent (just in case)
 :EndWhile
 nameв†ђ##.LeafNameвЌ•object вЌќ The text name of the object that I just created
 classв†ђ##.LeafNameвЌ•thisв†ђвЉѓвЋ•RSI вЌќ Namespace that I'm being called from gives me the name of the class and a reference to it
 :If isdefв†ђclassв‰Ў'def' вЌќ But if we're redefining a class from a 'def' variable, go get the previous settings instead of inferring them
     (class this)в†ђobject.(_class _Class) вЌќ This is how it was defined in the past - we'll keep it that way
 :EndIf
 object.(_self _name _class)в†ђ(parent._self,'.',name)name class вЌќ Set в€†WI system control information
