     :Select isdef~вЌ›/object._class вЌќ Create any needed "hidden" sub-objects (if not from a 'def')
вЌќ? We'd better watch out here! If we have to create our own hidden sub-objects, how will we know what creation-only parms we should be using?
вЌќ? Do we need to require the class to define these for us? And if so, how do we keep it simple enough for them to build (if possible/needed)?
     :Case 'Menu'
         вЌќ An APL+Win Menu object may be any of four Dyalog object-types depending on context.
